   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Response in Beirut, Lebanon</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The IRC emergency unit has launched an immediate response in Lebanon. The IRC will provide immediate cash and economic assistance to those impacted and displaced by the explosion in Beirut. The explosion - which killed 137 people and wounded 5,000 as of August 6th - has left an additional 300,000 people displaced. This devastation comes on top of an already looming threat of economic collapse, and threat of increasing scarcity of food connected to the COVID-19 outbreak.</narrative>
  </description>
